prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} image in the "Ice Cyan Megatype Action Poster Style" visual style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these style rules as concrete visual requirements:
- Composition: finished editorial action poster on an ice-white field with pale gray ghost words in the rear, deep-cyan oversized condensed headline through the center, a cutout photographic subject in front, and sparse chartreuse motion marks above all layers.
- Subject scale: one dominant subject should be centered slightly off-axis, enlarged, foreshortened, and cropped so a limb, tool, or prop projects toward the viewer and overlaps the headline.
- Typography: use ultra-condensed all-caps sans-serif type, deep petrol cyan for the main headline, very pale gray repeated ghost words behind it, a spaced vertical side label, a narrow barcode strip, tiny footer microcopy, and a compact burnt-orange date or issue tag.
- Color: keep the field mostly ice white and pale gray, use deep petrol cyan for type, neon chartreuse for abstract motion blurs and doodle bursts, and tiny warm orange details.
- Graphic elements: add soft chartreuse abstract blur disks near edges, a lime radial burst, a short wavy underline or zigzag, fine outline boxes, and a small barcode strip, all sparse and editorial.
- Photography: use crisp high-resolution action photography as a clean cutout collage element, with rim light, controlled shadow, sharp edges, realistic fabric or material detail, and polished magazine finish.

Avoid tennis subjects, tennis rackets, tennis balls, copied source text, copied source pose, source outfit, source year, brand marks, watermarks, QR codes, social media UI, dense clutter, flat vector-only rendering, 3D toy rendering, manga panel style, distorted anatomy, illegible letters, muddy noise, and compression artifacts.

Important content rule: match the style fidelity anchors first, then change the source content. Use new subjects, new scene details, new props or products, and new text while preserving the poster grammar.
